#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Вступ"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"Selection determines which elements will be the target of our actions. "
"Selections work on the current scene visible objects. Blender has advanced "
"selection methods. Both in *Object Mode* and in *Edit Mode*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:14
msgid "Selections and the Active Object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:16
msgid "Blender distinguishes between two different states of selection:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:20
msgid ""
"Unselected object in black, selected object in orange, and active object in "
"yellow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:23
msgid ""
"In *Object Mode* the last (de)selected item is called the \"Active Object\" "
"and is outlined in yellow (the others are orange). There is exactly one "
"active object at any time (even when nothing is selected)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:27
msgid ""
"Many actions in Blender use the active object as a reference (for example "
"linking operations). If you already have a selection and need to make a "
"different object the active one, simply re-select it with :kbd:`Shift-RMB`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/selecting/introduction.rst:31
msgid ""
"All other selected objects are just selected. You can select any number of "
"objects. In order to change a property or to perform an operation on all "
"selected objects (bones, and sequencer-strips) hold :kbd:`Alt`, while "
"confirming."
msgstr ""
